s are then offered a glimpse into the multifaceted world of Hindu worship, life-cycle rites, festivals, performances, gurus, and castes. The book’s final sections deal with the Hinduism that is emerging in diasporic North America and with issues of identity that face Hindus in India and around the world: militancy versus tolerance and the struggle between owning one’s own religion and sharing it with others. Contributors: Andrew Abbott, Michael Burawoy, Patricia Hill Collins, Barbara Ehrenreich, Evelyn Nakano Glenn, Sharon Hays, Douglas Massey, Joya Misra, Orlando Patterson, Frances Fox Piven, Lynn Smith-Lovin, Judith Stacey, Arthur Stinchcombe, Alain Touraine, Immanuel Wallerstein, William Julius Wilson, Robert Zussman  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aHinduismxCustoms and practices. 0aHinduismxSocial aspects. 0aReligious lifexHinduism. 7aRELIGION / Hinduism / General.2bisacsh1 aAcharya, Kala, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAntarjanam, Lalitambika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBahadur, Om Lata, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBharati, Agehananda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCase, Margaret H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChakravarti, Sitansu S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEck, Diana L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aErndl, Kathleen M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoswami, Shrivatsa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHallstrom, Lisa Lassell, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHawley, John Stratton, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vo